HEADWORD: Temperer
<hw>Tem"per*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, tempers; specifically, a machine in which lime, cement, stone,
etc., are mixed with water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

